    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.22.4"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">4</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">W.R. POAGE
                        <lb/>
                    CONGRESSMAN
                        <lb/>
                    11TH TEXAS DISTRICT
                
                    MEMBER
                        <lb/>
                    COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE</hi>
    
                    Congress of the United States
                        <lb/>
                    House of Representatives
                        <lb/>
                    Washington, <hi rend="caps">D.C.</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <note type="curatorial">An<unclear>s</unclear>d.
                    Apr 19</note>
                <note><hi rend="caps">WRP</hi></note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 12, 1948</dateline>
                
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Hon. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Branson, Missouri</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute> 
                </opener>
                <p>I would like very much to have copies of four of your poems, and am writing to you personally to request that you be kind enough to autograph each for me. They are
                    <list>
                        <item>"The Song of Three Friends"</item>
                        <item>"The Song of Hugh Glass"</item>
                        <item>"The Song of the Indian Wars" and </item>
                        <item>"The Song of Jed Smith".</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                
                <p>I heard you speak at Baylor University, Waco, Texas years ago, but at that time I did not have the money to buy your works. Now that I do have the money I would appreciate your kindness in sending them, with a statement covering the cost. I shall appreciate this greatly.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With all good wishes, I am</salute>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                    <signed>W. R. Poage.</signed>
                    <signed>W. R. Poage, Congressman
                    11th Texas District</signed>
                
                    <note>WRP:gnd</note>
                
                    <note>Postage Paid</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
